The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also uses information theoretic arguments, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The smooth rectangle bound is a lower bound method used in communication complexity, which suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper deals with relations and functions used to show exponential separations between classical and quantum communication complexity, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
